Package: countmissing
Title: Count Missing Values For All Columns By Group
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Arabella", "Helgason", email = "ahelg18@student.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Given a data frame `data` and a column `group`, `count_all_missing_by_group()` creates
  a new data frame with one row per level of `group`. The first column of the output data frame
  contains the levels of `group`, and the rest of the columns contain the number of missing values for
  all columns in `data` except `group`.
